Reading the table:
 EOD: max(TPR_gap, FPR_gap); lower = fairer
 TPR_gap / FPR_gap: which error rate the constraint actually equalised
 recall_TPR: the cost paid; watch how far it drops from baseline
 DI_ratio: closer to 1.0 = fairer selection rates
 indiv_fair: closer to 1 = similar people scored similarly

Impossibility note: with unequal base rates, calibrated eq-odds can
equalise one error rate (the chosen constraint) only by widening the other.
